vectorData.altText: That’s right!  Cingulum is the association fibre bundle that courses above and then below the corpus callosum.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

The corpus callosum is composed of commissural fibres. Identify its rostrum, genu, body and splenium.  Remove portions of the cingulum adjacent to the splenium and genu of the corpus callosum laterally to expose the forceps major and forceps minor.

R. cerebral hemisphere, medial view.
From Serial Dissections of the Human Brain, by Carlton G. Smith, M.D., Ph.D., © 1981 by Gage.
On the MEDIAL SURFACE of the cerebral hemisphere, use your scalpel handle to scrape off

the cortex of the cingulate and parahippocampal gyri to expose the association fibres that make up the cingulum.  Note how the cingulum courses above the corpus callosum and into the parahippocampal gyrus and uncus.
